verbs.description: missionarize (third-person singular simple present missionarizes, present participle missionarizing, simple past and past participle missionarized)

examples: That religion is dead which does not missionarize. No worse objection can be made to the free-thinkers of to-day, who frequently boast of representing the world-conception of the cultured and the intelligent, than their utter want of the missionarizing spirit.
